s' Association |location=Mount Vernon, Virginia |year=2001 |isbn=978-0-931917-38-7 }}\n\n===For young readers===\n* {{cite book |last=Delano |first=Marfe Ferguson |title=Master George's People: George Washington, His Slaves, and His Revolutionary Transformation |url=https://archive.org/details/mastergeorgespeo0000dela |url-access=registration |publisher=National Geographic |location=Boone, Iowa |year=2013 |isbn=978-1-4263-0759-1 }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Dunbar |first1=Erica Armstrong |last2=Van Cleve |first2=Kathleen |lastauthoramp=y |title=Never Caught, the Story of Ona Judge: George and Martha Washington's Courageous Slave Who Dared to Run Away; Young Readers Edition |publisher=Simon & Schuster |location=New York, New York |year=2019 |isbn=978-1-5344-1617-8 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Levy |first=Janet |title=Slavery at Mount Vernon |publisher=Gareth Stevens Publishing |location=New York, New York |year=2016 |isbn=978-1-4824-5805-3 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Rinaldi |first=Ann |title=Taking Liberty: The Story of Oney Judge, George Washington's Runaway Slave |publisher=Simon & Schuster |location=New York, New York |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-689-85187-2 }}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://founders.archives.gov/documents/Washington/06-04-02-0404-0001 George Washington's will]\n* [https://www.mountvernon.org/george-washington/slavery/ Mount Vernon website pages on slavery]\n* [https://www.mountvernon.org/george-washington/slavery/washingtons-changing-views-on-slavery/ Mount Vernon website page on the evolution of Washington's views on slavery] \n* [http://www.ushistory.org/presidentshouse/slaves/index.php Slavery at the President's House in Philadelphia]\n\n{{George Washington}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Washington, George}}\n[[Category:American slave owners]]\n[[Category:George Washington]]\n[[Category:History of slavery in Virginia]]\n[[Category:Slavery in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Factotem", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMulattoes:ce per FAC", "url_page": "//en