All Access]] respectively, created by [[Robert King (writer)|Robert]] and [[Michelle King]]. ''The Good Wife'' follows the political, professional, and personal life of [[Alicia Florrick]] ([[Julianna Margulies]]), a political \"good wife\" who is thrust back into the workplace after over a decade after her husband, Peter Florrick ([[Chris Noth]]), a local [[Chicago]] [[politician]], is arrested on corruption charged following a highly publicized sex scandal.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=The Good Wife - Cast & Crew |url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/the-good-wife/cast/297522/ |magazine=[[TV Guide]] |access-date=May 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Good Wife (Cast)|url=http://www.tv.com/shows/the-good-wife/cast/|website=TV.com|accessdate=May 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Good Wife Cast|url=https://www.cbs.com/shows/the_good_wife/cast/|website=cbs.com|publisher=[[CBS Television]]|accessdate=May 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Stanhope|first1=Kate|title='The Good Wife': What's Next for the Cast|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/good-wife-whats-next-cast-892173|website=hollywoodreporter.com|publisher=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=May 9, 2018}}</ref> ''The Good Fight'' follows Alicia's former colleagues [[Diane Lockhart]] ([[Christine Baranski]]) and Lucca Quinn ([[Cush Jumbo]]) contending with political and legal challenges in a [[Trump era|new political environment]] as they continue their careers at a left-wing, African American\u2013owned law firm.\n\n==Main==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14%;\" scope=\"col\"| Actor\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14%;\" scope=\"col\"| Character\n! colspan=\"7\" | ''The Good Wife''\n! colspan=\"4\" | ''The Good Fight''\n|-\n! style=\"width:7%;\" scope=\"col\" | [[The Good Wife (season 1)|1]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\" scope=\"col\" | [[The Good Wife (season 2)|2]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\" scope=\"col\" | [[The Good Wife (se